Unless otherwise provided for in this Charter or by the Connecticut General Statutes, A. All members of Town Boards shall be electors of the Town and shall have such other qualifications as the Board of Selectmen may provide. B. Members of Town Boards shall serve without compensation, except that just and ordinary expenses incurred by said members in the performance of their duties cemay be reimbursed, provided that such appropriation has been authorized for that purpose.